RUN_THIS_CODE

Follow these exact steps to start the Swing Score web UI and related helpers.
Copy-paste each command into the terminal (zsh) while in the project root.

1) ACTIVATE THE VENV
   source .venv/bin/activate

2) INSTALL MINIMAL DEPENDENCIES (only if you haven't already)
   pip install flask plotly tabulate requests pandas

3) START THE FLASK DEV SERVER (web UI)
   python -m backend.app

   Then open this URL in your browser:
   http://127.0.0.1:5000/

ALTERNATIVES / HELPERS

- Run the interactive terminal UI (prompts for state):
  python -m backend.interactive

- Run the simple shell menu (choose a state from a numbered list):
  chmod +x scripts/state_menu.sh   # one-time if needed
  ./scripts/state_menu.sh

- Non-interactive quick test (simulate choosing PA and decline map):
  printf "6\nn\n" | ./scripts/state_menu.sh

- Export full CSV for a state (example: PA):
  python -m backend.export_full_state --state PA --out outputs/PA_all_counties.csv

- Generate a Plotly map from a CSV (example: PA):
  python -m backend.plotly_map --state PA --input outputs/PA_all_counties.csv --out outputs

TROUBLESHOOTING NOTES
- If you see: "the following arguments are required: --state/-s" â€” you tried to run the map script without the required --state flag. Use the command above or use the web UI / shell menu instead.
- If the web page looks empty, confirm that outputs/PA_all_counties.csv exists and that `swingscorejsons/counties.geojson` is present (the app will download it if not).
- If you get ImportError for Flask or Plotly, run the pip install command in step 2.

If anything fails, copy the terminal output and paste it here and I'll help debug.
